sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User Browser
    participant Route as OpenShift Route<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant OAuth as OAuth Proxy Sidecar<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Jupyter as JupyterLab Container<br/>8888/TCP HTTP
    participant K8sAPI as OpenShift API<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.3
    participant PyPI as PyPI CDN<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant S3 as S3 Storage<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant ModelReg as Model Registry<br/>8080/TCP HTTP mTLS
    participant KFP as Kubeflow Pipelines<br/>8888/TCP HTTP
    participant RuntimePod as Runtime Image Pod

    rect rgb(220, 240, 255)
        Note over User,Jupyter: Flow 1: User Accessing Notebook Workbench
        User->>Route: HTTPS Request<br/>Auth: OpenShift Session Cookie
        Route->>OAuth: Forward (Re-encrypt TLS)<br/>Port 8443/TCP
        OAuth->>OAuth: Validate OAuth Token
        OAuth->>Jupyter: HTTP Request<br/>Port 8888/TCP<br/>Proxy-injected headers
        Jupyter->>K8sAPI: Cluster Operations<br/>Service Account Token
        Jupyter-->>OAuth: Response
        OAuth-->>Route: Response
        Route-->>User: HTTPS Response
    end

    rect rgb(255, 245, 220)
        Note over Jupyter,PyPI: Flow 2: Package Installation
        Jupyter->>PyPI: pip install request<br/>HTTPS/443
        PyPI-->>Jupyter: Python packages
        Jupyter->>Jupyter: Install to local filesystem<br/>POSIX permissions
    end

    rect rgb(240, 255, 240)
        Note over Jupyter,RuntimePod: Flow 3: Elyra Pipeline Execution
        Jupyter->>KFP: Submit pipeline<br/>Bearer Token
        KFP->>K8sAPI: Create runtime pod<br/>Service Account Token
        K8sAPI->>RuntimePod: Schedule pod
        RuntimePod->>S3: Download data/model<br/>AWS Credentials
        RuntimePod->>RuntimePod: Execute notebook task
        RuntimePod->>S3: Upload results<br/>AWS Credentials
        RuntimePod->>KFP: Status update<br/>Bearer Token
        KFP-->>Jupyter: Pipeline complete
    end

    rect rgb(255, 240, 245)
        Note over Jupyter,ModelReg: Flow 4: Model Training and Registration
        Jupyter->>S3: Fetch training data<br/>AWS Credentials
        Jupyter->>Jupyter: Train model<br/>GPU acceleration
        Jupyter->>ModelReg: Register model<br/>mTLS Service Account
        ModelReg->>S3: Store model artifacts<br/>AWS Credentials
        ModelReg-->>Jupyter: Model ID
    end
